The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Bangalore, Aug. 29: Infrastructure developer GMR Group today announced a major organisational restructuring to tap growth opportunities in India and abroad. Under the structure, chairman and managing director G.M. Rao will assume the role of group chairman, while the group will have four chairmen to lead individual businesses. Moreover, it will have professional CEOs to head various individual businesses. 

 New Delhi, Aug. 29: Import of finished carbon steel in the country during April-July this year rose 60.2 per cent to 1.45 million tonnes from 0.905 million tonnes in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal. Steel exports during the period also grew 7.2 per cent to 1.750 million tonnes.

 New Delhi, Aug. 29: The Infrastructure Development Finance Corporation (IDFC) will raise Rs 12,000-14,000 crore debt in this fiscal from the domestic debt market to fund infrastructure projects in the country.

 Mumbai, Aug. 29: The National Stock Exchange has become the worlds second fastest-growing bourse in terms of number of listed companies, while the BSE has consolidated its position as the biggest bourse.

 Mumbai, Aug. 29: Pidilite Industries has received shareholders approval for merger of the vinyl acetate monomer manufacturing unit of Vinyl Chemicals (India) at Mahad with itself.




